WE NEED YOUR HELP!
In an effort to keep students connected, engaged, and safe as we begin to transition to a blended learning model in the Fall, we are raising money to help provide each student with a set of new headphones. This will give them just one of the many tools they need to be successful in a school environment where digital platforms will continue to be essential.

If you want to help you can make a donation or pass it along!

Thank you in advance to anyone able to help ❤️

post_text:
As a school community, we stand in solidarity with our students, staff, and families of color and we pledge to do our part to support justice for all people, not only in our words, but also in our actions. Silence about the problems of racism and injustice can no longer be an option for those who strive to show Humility, Empowerment, Aspiration, Responsibility, Teamwork and Scholarship. We will actively seek to continue to educate ourselves, staff and students, as we all have much to learn and to grow.

#blacklivesmatter #blackexcellance
#allpowertothepeople #blm #eastflatbush
#canarsie #nyccharterschools #tnaacs #tnaacscommunity

PHASE 1 REOPENING DATE June 8th PROJECTED FOR NEW YORK CITY.

The city is currently working on increasing its contact tracing capacity and the share of total beds available so that it can meet the seven metrics that are required for the complete reopening of a region.

The industries that can reopen:
Construction
Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing, and Hunting
Retail (limited to curbside or in-store pick-up or drop-off)
Manufacturing
Wholesale Trade

COVID-19 safety measures must still be observed. If curbside pick-up is not an option for retailers, in-store pick-ups can't exceed a 50% capacity.

https://forward.ny.gov/regional-unpause-dashboard

post_text:
Teachers, you inspire us every day. With school closures, we're seeing more people everywhere show how they cherish teachers. To celebrate this, we’re launching #ThankATeacherChallenge and giving away $100,000 in TpT gift cards* to teachers this Teacher Appreciation Week.

Here’s how you can participate:

Share your moment of teacher appreciation on Instagram, FB or Twitter using #ThankATeacherChallenge. We want to see it all — from "thank you" signs in your front yard to messages of encouragement to your classes.

Tag Teachers Pay Teachers and nominate another teacher to join the challenge by tagging them, too!

Fill out this form ( https://bit.ly/3d36XKH ) to be entered to receive one of 10,000 $10 TpT gift cards, while supplies last.

Learn More https://bit.ly/2SmMY1y

Our Streets, Out Stories!

Brooklyn Public Library is calling for submissions to its local oral history archive, Our Streets, Our Stories. At this moment in time, we have an opportunity to collect testimonies and memories of the crisis as it is unfolding so that future Brooklynites can understand the pandemic at a local level. If you are a healthcare worker, a teacher, a student, a parent, a community member, a first responder, an essential worker, a senior, or if you are incarcerated or have a loved one who is incarcerated, we want to hear from you. If you are a Brooklynite, this story is your story.

https://www.bklynlibrary.org/podcasts/oral-histories

Create your own terrarium in honor of today.
To make your terrariums you'll need:

A glass bowl or a large glass jar

Pebbles

Activated charcoal (available at pet stores)

Potting soil

Succulents, air plants, or other plants

Decorative rocks, figures, etc.

Combine and enjoy the beauty

"The New York City Department of Education is committed to making three free meals available daily for any New Yorker."

Meals can be picked up Monday - Friday between the hours of 7:30am -1:30pm.

No ID required.
All adults and children can pick up 3 meals a day at one time.
Vegetarian and Halal meals available.
No one will be turned away.

Visit the interactive Map to find a location near you.
https://bit.ly/2wjDn3U

post_text:
Team Angelou had their first @skypeascientist meeting today with Dr. Ariangela Kozik @kozimicrobe, a Research Fellow at Huang Microbiome Lab at University of Michigan. Students watched a number of videos to prepare for the call. They were excited to learn about about her studies surrounding “the communities of microorganisms” focusing on asthma. Dr. Kozik also shared her inspiration which lead her to become a scientist and the support from her family and teachers.

#scicomm #tnaacs #charterschool #elementaryschool #community #wearebettertogether #remotelearning #leadbyexample #servingthefuture #tnaacsfamily #moretocome #wegotyou #technology

All Licenses, Non Driver ID's, and Registrations with an expiration date of March 1, 2020 or later are extended until further notice.

A special thank you to Children of Light Food Pantry who work throughout the year in our community to provide families much needed support.

"I have found that among its benefits, giving liberates the soul of the giver.” ~ Maya Angelou
